
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `ciptool` baraye modiriat va dastkari file-haye CIP (Catalog Interchange Protocol) estefade mishavad. In dastoor be shoma komak mikonad etela'at file-haye CIP ra bebinid, tabdil konid va validate konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `ciptool info <file.cip>`  --> ℹ️ Namayesh etela'at asasi dar morede yek file CIP.
    🔹 `ciptool validate <file.cip>`  --> ✅ Check kardan dorosti va etebare yek file CIP.
    🔹 `ciptool convert <input.cip> <output.xml>` --> 🔄 Tabdil yek file CIP be format XML.
    🔹 `ciptool --help` --> ❓ Namayesh rahnamaye kamel baraye hameye gozine-ha.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ ciptool info example.cip

    🔹 Namayesh etela'ate asasi dar morede file `example.cip`.

    $ ciptool validate mycatalog.cip

    🔹 Check kardan dorosti va etebare file `mycatalog.cip`.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ ciptool info product.cip | grep "Product Name"

    🔹 Peyda kardan va namayesh dadane name mahsool az file `product.cip`.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `ciptool` command is used to manage and manipulate CIP (Catalog Interchange Protocol) files. It allows you to view information, validate, and convert CIP files.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `ciptool info <file.cip>`  --> ℹ️ Display basic information about a CIP file.
    🔹 `ciptool validate <file.cip>`  --> ✅ Validate the integrity and correctness of a CIP file.
    🔹 `ciptool convert <input.cip> <output.xml>` --> 🔄 Convert a CIP file to XML format.
    🔹 `ciptool --help` --> ❓ Display the complete help manual with all options.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ ciptool info example.cip

    🔹 Display basic information about the `example.cip` file.

    $ ciptool validate mycatalog.cip

    🔹 Check the integrity and correctness of the `mycatalog.cip` file.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ ciptool info product.cip | grep "Product Name"

    🔹 Find and display the product name from the `product.cip` file.
